    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in ue_init_config_request when called multiple times\n\n### Summary\nThe `ue_init_config_request` function in the NR MAC UE was allocating memory for `dl_config_request` and `ul_config_request` arrays without checking if they were already allocated. This caused memory leaks when the function was called multiple times, such as during reconfiguration procedures.\n\nThis fix ensures proper memory management by checking for existing allocations and freeing them before reallocating.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/config_ue.c`: Added proper memory management in `ue_init_config_request` function to prevent leaks when called multiple times\n- Fixed a typo in a comment in the same file\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Initialize a UE MAC instance\n2. Call `ue_init_config_request` with a specific SCS\n3. Call `ue_init_config_request` again with the same or different SCS\n4. Observe memory leak due to previous allocations not being freed\n\nThe symptom is increased memory usage over time during UE reconfiguration procedures.\n"
}